@startuml Evaluation Model - End-to-End Latency
!theme plain

title End-to-End Latency vs Number of Vehicles

' Simulation data
!define DATA_50  45
!define DATA_100 52
!define DATA_200 68
!define DATA_500 95
!define DATA_1000 138
!define DATA_2000 205

scale 800 width

' Line chart
!procedure $plot($x, $y, $label)
    rectangle "$label\n$y ms" as point$x <<data>>
!endprocedure

package "E2E Latency (ms)" {
    rectangle "50 vehicles\n45ms" as p50 #lightgreen
    rectangle "100 vehicles\n52ms" as p100 #lightgreen
    rectangle "200 vehicles\n68ms" as p200 #yellow
    rectangle "500 vehicles\n95ms" as p500 #orange
    rectangle "1000 vehicles\n138ms" as p1000 #orange
    rectangle "2000 vehicles\n205ms" as p2000 #red
}

p50 -[hidden]right-> p100
p100 -[hidden]right-> p200
p200 -[hidden]right-> p500
p500 -[hidden]right-> p1000
p1000 -[hidden]right-> p2000

note bottom
    **Latency Metrics:**

    **Total Time Components:**
    • Generation and signature: 5-8ms
    • V2I transmission: 10-15ms
    • Pre-validation (RSU): 8-12ms
    • Network propagation: 15-30ms
    • Consensus (PBFT): 20-100ms
    • Ledger recording: 5-10ms

    **Analysis:**
    ✓ Up to 200 vehicles: Acceptable latency (<100ms)
    ⚠ 500-1000 vehicles: Moderate latency
    ✗ >2000 vehicles: Requires optimization

    **ITS Requirement:** Maximum latency < 100ms
end note

@enduml
